Jordan Insurance Companies Profit Doubles, Premiums Rise in 2010

-- B y   M o h a m m a d   T a y s e e r
-- 
2011-06-20T18:45:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/jordan-insurance-companies-profit-doubles-premiums-rise-in-2010.html
Jordan’s insurance companies more
than doubled their profit last year as premiums rose by 12
percent to 408.6 million dinars ($576 million) compared with
2009, the Insurance Commission of Jordan said.  The kingdom’s insurance companies made 15.9 million dinars
in profits before tax in 2010 compared with 7.3 million dinars
in 2009, a  report  on the commission’s website said.  The insurance sector’s contribution to the gross domestic
product in 2010 reached 2.1 percent compared with 2.05 percent
in 2009, it said. Jordan has 28 licensed insurance companies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nayla Razzouk in Beirut at 
 nrazzouk2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Riad Hamade at 
 rhamade@bloomberg.net  